'''Bury the Hatchet''' is an [[American English]] [[colloquialism]] meaning "to make peace."  The phrase is an allusion to the figurative or literal practice of putting away the [[tomahawk]] at the cessation of hostilities among or by [[Native Americans]] in the Eastern United States.

